sDssnBUI9PeTyg==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating class loading**\\n\\nI'm considering whether the Execute class loaded its static block. It could depend on the environment not being \\\"openvms\\\" or OS/2. I wonder if tests failed to load Execute in the dynamic report, possibly due to the ProcessDestroyerTest being unrelated. I should create an ExecuteTest to ensure it loads and runs correctly using Java13CommandLauncher. Since the static initialization happens once upon class loading, a dedicated test file might be sufficient. I need to check build conventions as well.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_sI3BJoDq6C58kHJZuYD5TG8h|fc_0a28a1dfb9d80ab30169f578e17e0c81969bdba3e22b82b383", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/ant/ant/1.6/build.gradle", "limit": 200}}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_JMJliVyRSf3SIHW2w4MY9oF6|fc_0a28a1dfb9d80ab30169f578e17e1c8196b6b52e46fcce1946", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/ant/ant/1.6/src/test/java/ant/ant/ProcessDestroyerTest.java", "limit": 120}}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_UcnYtUepCiIuQJYrtik8h4HH|fc_0a28a1dfb9d80ab30169f578e17e3081969948a2eae6132786", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "metadata/ant/ant/1.6/reachability-metadata.json", "limit": 200}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3190, "output": 449, "cacheRead": 14336, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 17975, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777694937223, "responseId": "resp_0a28a1dfb9d80ab30169f578d990048196be9e464e392ad7c6"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_sI3BJoDq6C58kHJZuYD5TG8h|fc_0a28a1dfb9d80ab30169f578e17e0c81969bdba3e22b82b383", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\nplugins {\n    id \"org.graalvm.internal.tck\"\n}\n\nString libraryVersion = tck.testedLibraryVersion.get()\n\ndependencies {\n    testImplementation \"ant:ant:$libraryVersion\"\n    testImplementation \"ant:ant-launcher:$libraryVersion\"\n    testImplementation \"ant:ant-nodeps:$libraryVersion\"\n    testImplementation \"ant:ant-trax:$libraryVersion\"\n    testImplementation \"ant:ant-xalan1:$libraryVersion\"\n    testImplementation \"ant:ant-xslp:$libraryVersion\"\n    testImplementation 'bcel:bcel:5.1'\n    testImplementation 'xml-resolver:xml-resolver:1.2'\n    testImplementation 'org.assertj:assertj-core:3.22.0'\n}\n\ntasks.withType(Test).configureEach {\n    jvmArgs '-Dfile.encoding=ISO-8859-1'\n}\n\ngraalvmNative {\n    binaries {\n        test {\n            buildArgs('-Dfile.encoding=ISO-8859-1')\n            runtimeArgs('-Dfile.encoding=ISO-8859-1')\n            runtimeArgs(\"-Djava.class.path=${sourceSets.test.runtimeClasspath.asPath}\")\n        }\n    }\n    agent {\n        defaultMode = \"conditional\"\n        modes {\n            conditional {\n                userCodeFilterPath = \"user-code-filter.json\"\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777694945698}, {"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_JMJliVyRSf3SIHW2w4MY9oF6|fc_0a28a1dfb9d80ab30169f578e17e1c8196b6b52e46fcce1946", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage ant.ant;\n\nimport java.io.File;\nimport java.io.IOException;\n\nimport org.apache.tools.ant.taskdefs.Execute;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class ProcessDestroyerTest {\n    @Test\n    void executeRegistersAndUnregistersShutdownHookAroundProcess() throws IOException {\n        Execute execute = new Execute();\n        execute.setCommandline(new String[] {javaExecutable(), \"-version\"});\n\n        int exitCode = execute.execute();\n\n        assertThat(exitCode).isZero();\n        assertThat(execute.getExitValue()).isZero();\n        assertThat(Execute.isFailure(exitCode)).isFalse();\n    }\n\n    private static String javaExecutable() {\n        String executableName = isWindows() ? \"java.exe\" : \"java\";\n        String javaHome = System.getProperty(\"java.home\");\n        if (javaHome != null) {\n            File executable = new File(new File(javaHome, \"bin\"), executableName);\n            if (executable.isFile()) {\n                return executable.getAbsolutePath();\n            }\n        }\n        return executableName;\n    }\n\n    private static boolean isWindows() {\n        return System.getProperty(\"os.name\", \"\").toLowerCase().contains(\"win\");\n    }\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777694945699}, {"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_UcnYtUepCiIuQJYrtik8h4HH|fc_0a28a1dfb9d80ab30169f578e17e3081969948a2eae6132786", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "{}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777694945699}]}
