ns like `Execute` seem valid, but I might not have covered everything. The nested initializer in the test class and its `$` naming complicate things. Perhaps creating a helper class without the `$`, loaded via `ServiceLoader`, could work? I wonder if a top-level class file can still function without overlap in test files. Using `URLClassLoader` might help avoid reflection issues while loading effectively.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_JS2VsuEvmMxqGjDd33bqN6k6|fc_0a28a1dfb9d80ab30169f57aab9ff88196aeab0491faf2da6d", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "cat tests/src/ant/ant/1.6/build/test-results/test/testlist/*.txt | nl -ba | sed -n '1,80p'", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 832, "output": 2276, "cacheRead": 48128, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 51236, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777695370629, "responseId": "resp_0a28a1dfb9d80ab30169f57a8b30ac8196b911da9f9d85d13b"}}
